<section id="Section605037">
  <title>
<indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>sales orders</primary>
      <secondary>list open</secondary>
    </indexterm>List Open Sales Orders</title>
  <para>A Sales Order appears on the List Open Sales Orders screen if one or
  more of its Line Items remains open. Once all Line Items for a Sales Order
  have been closed, the Sales Order will no longer appear on the list.
  Typically, Sales Order Line Items are closed when the Order is selected for
  billing. To display open Sales Orders by Warehouse, select the "Open Sales
  Orders" option. The following screen will appear:</para>
  <para>
<screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata id="Graphic523353" fileref="images/openSalesOrders.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption id="Caption519186">Open Sales Orders Master List</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
</para>
  <para>When displaying open Sales Orders, you are presented with the
  following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry role="openmfg">
      <term>All Warehouses</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be1f8">
        <para>Select to display a list of open Sales Orders for all
        Warehouses.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry role="openmfg">
      <term>Selected</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be21c">
        <para>Specify Warehouse whose open Sales Orders you want to
        display.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Sales Orders</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be264">
        <para>Display lists open Sales Orders.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>To the far right of the screen, the following buttons are
  available:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>CLOSE</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be2d0">
        <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
        desktop.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>PRINT</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be318">
        <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>NEW</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x18be360">
        <para>Opens screen for creating a new Sales Order.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>VIEW</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersVIEW">
        <para>Highlight a Sales Order and then select this button to reach a
        read-only view of the "Edit" screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>COPY</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersCOPY">
        <para>Highlight a Sales Order and then select this button to create a
        new Sales Order which duplicates the source Sales Order.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>EDIT</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersEDIT">
        <para>Enables you to edit highlighted Sales Order. The edit screen is
        the same as that for creating a new Sales Order--except that when
        editing, the fields will contain Sales Order information.
        Double-clicking on a Sales Order will also bring you to the editing
        screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>DELETE</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersDELETE">
        <para>Highlight a Sales Order and then select this button to remove
        the Sales Order from the master list</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>Right-clicking on an Order in the Sales Orders list enables you to
  select from the following menu options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Edit</term>
      <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xpointer="element(openSalesOrdersEDIT)"/>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>View</term>
      <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xpointer="element(openSalesOrdersVIEW)"/>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Copy</term>
      <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xpointer="element(openSalesOrdersCOPY)"/>
    </varlistentry>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickReschedule)"/>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Delete</term>
      <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xpointer="element(openSalesOrdersDELETE)"/>
    </varlistentry>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickPrintPackingList)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickAddtoPackingListBatch)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickScheduleSOforEmailDelivery)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml" xpointer="element(rightclickPrintSalesOrderForm)"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../widgets/xtreewidget.xml" xpointer="element(xtreewidget.menu.exportcontents)"/>
  </variablelist>
</section>
